  "prompt": "Can we do court marriage in any state?",
  "response": "Court marriage laws can vary by state in India. Here are some key points:\n\n1. General Provisions:\n- Court marriage is possible in most states\n- Governed by the Special Marriage Act, 1954\n- Applicable to all Indian citizens across religions\n\n2. Requirements:\n- Minimum age: 21 years for males, 18 for females\n- Both parties must be legally eligible to marry\n- Consent of both parties\n- Notice period of 30 days before marriage\n\n3. Process:\n- File application at Marriage Registration Office\n- Submit required documents\n- Appear before Marriage Officer\n- Complete registration formalities\n\n4. State-specific variations:\n- Some states have slightly different procedural requirements\n- Documentation might vary slightly\n- Processing time can differ\n\n5. Documents typically needed:\n- Age proof\n- Identity proof\n- Address proof\n- Passport-sized photographs\n- Affidavit of marital status\n- Divorce/death certificate (if applicable)\n\n6. Recommended steps:\n- Check local Marriage Registration Office guidelines\n- Verify specific state requirements\n- Prepare all necessary documents\n- Follow prescribed procedure\n\nAlways consult local authorities or a legal expert for precise, up-to-date information specific to your state.",
